      "comment": "GINGERIFFIC (9) comes here third-up off a solid run at Rockingham last time out, missing out by 3.5L. Expected to be better again today and she still possesses some upside being a lightly raced 3YO. Can improve again now and can get back to winning ways. QUICK COOKIE (7) missed by 3.1L last start following a better run at York the start prior. Back to a race of this level is a big tick for her and she has the speed to roll across from the draw. Can make an impression. SANSANEE (8) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1000m at Albany, beaten 10 lengths into eighth after being prominent at the corner. Won't find this as tough so she is set to turn things around. CALATHINITE (2) has not raced since he finished eighth over 1200m at Pinjarra on December 11. Is lightly raced and looks forward enough after a solid recent trial. One of the genuine contenders. PERCUSSION PRINCE (10) can fire a shot on resumption.",
